15:19.168 --> 15:20.503
‐ Yeah, I know.

15:20.503 --> 15:23.131
This painting just ain't singin'
like the last one.

15:23.131 --> 15:25.967
‐ Now, now, Synth, the last thing
I want you to think

15:25.967 --> 15:27.552
is that I'm disappointed.

15:28.261 --> 15:30.513
So for that reason,
I'm going to walk away now.

15:32.306 --> 15:33.808
‐ Huh…

15:37.145 --> 15:38.062
‐ Hmm…

15:38.062 --> 15:39.105
Uh, huh!

15:39.105 --> 15:42.108
♪

15:54.162 --> 15:56.789
‐ And I want those confetti reports
on my desk by noon.

15:58.082 --> 16:00.168
SKY TORONTO:
By all that's Trolly…

16:00.626 --> 16:03.004
I don't know how I missed it before:

16:03.004 --> 16:06.507
this painting sings even more beautifully
than Synth's first.

16:06.883 --> 16:10.261
Why, I'm so stunned, I have half a mind
to spit‐take this cocoa.

16:11.137 --> 16:12.346
Spit‐take this cocoa.

16:14.724 --> 16:15.808
‐ Yes!
‐ Yes!

16:15.808 --> 16:20.646
‐ When word gets out about the newly
discovered brilliance of this painting,

16:20.646 --> 16:23.983
everyone in TrollsTopia
will want a "Synth" on their wall.

16:24.609 --> 16:25.693
‐ "Everyone"?

16:26.736 --> 16:29.030
‐ Ah, I'm okay being done with painting.

16:29.405 --> 16:32.325
Now I have more time
to stop and smell the seaweed.

16:34.410 --> 16:36.037
Hmm.

16:36.037 --> 16:37.747
Seaweed smells gross.

16:37.872 --> 16:38.706
Huh?

16:42.752 --> 16:44.003
‐ I want one too!

16:44.629 --> 16:47.340
‐ Looks like Synth's
got a lotta painting to do.

16:47.340 --> 16:50.259
‐ Which means you've got
a lot of repainting to do.

16:50.801 --> 16:51.928
[ nervous laugh ]

16:53.054 --> 16:54.263
‐ Hmm…

16:54.263 --> 16:57.350
♪

